<Placemark><name>🇸🇩 Sudan Civil War — SAF vs. RSF</name>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Sudan Civil War — SAF vs. RSF</b><br/><b>Subregion:</b> Horn / NE Africa<br/><b>Category:</b> MILITARY | <b>Domain:</b> Civil War / Genocide<br/><b>Severity:</b> CRITICAL | <b>Status:</b> ACTIVE<br/><b>Index:</b> 97/100 (Δ +1)<br/><b>Human cost:</b> 150,000+ dead; El Fasher 6,000 in 72h<br/><b>Note:</b> RSF declared rival "Peace Government" + issued pre-assault appeal to El Obeid residents to stay home · 300+ killed on Bara corridor first half of July · 350,000 newly displaced across Greater Kordofan since May · UN Türk: "We have seen this playbook before" · HRC session closes JUL 7 · EU sanctioned 7 incl. Hemedti's brother · first RSF war-crimes case filed in Kenya<br/><b>Gov sources:</b> UN Security Council: Panel of Experts documents arms flows; genocide-determination pressure | US State Dept: Genocide determination (Jan 2025); Boulos envoy shuttle; UNSC briefing | UK FCDO: El Obeid 'on the precipice of an atrocity'; 29-nation coalition | EU Council: Sanctions on 7 individuals incl. Algoney Hamdan Dagalo (Hemedti's brother) | UN OHCHR (Türk): 'Stop this madness' — imminent El Obeid offensive risks serious international crimes; El Fasher playbook warning<br/><b>Mil leverage:</b> UAE: RSF supply — drones, arms, mercenaries; Ethiopia training camp [HIGH] | US/UK/France: Arms sales + cover for UAE — the unused counter-lever [HIGH] | RSF (Hemedti): Encirclement of El Obeid; Darfur + Kordofan control [HIGH] | SAF (Burhan): Center/east + Nile valley; air force [MED]<br/><b>Econ leverage:</b> UAE (Gold + arms channel) [HIGH]: RSF gold exports + supply architecture; Reuters-confirmed Ethiopia camp; the unpulled US counter-lever<br/><b>Assessment:</b> Sudan rises to its highest-ever 97. The RSF crossed from massing to marching: a declared rival 'Peace Government,' sweeping advances toward El Obeid from all directions, and the signature pre-assault instruction to residents to 'remain in their homes.' Yale/ACLED's warning that this could exceed El Fasher is now the live scenario, with 300+ dead on the Bara corridor and 350,000 newly displaced. The HRC session closes July 7 — the atrocity-prevention window and the assault timeline have converged. The UAE lever remains unpulled.<br/><i>v15.0 · Week 12</i>]]></description><styleUrl>#s-military</styleUrl>
