<Placemark><name>🇬🇭 Ghana — Frontier State + Galamsey Nexus</name>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Ghana — Frontier State + Galamsey Nexus</b><br/><b>Subregion:</b> Coastal Frontier<br/><b>Category:</b> MILITARY | <b>Domain:</b> Pre-Insurgency / Organized Crime<br/><b>Severity:</b> MEDIUM | <b>Status:</b> ESCALATING<br/><b>Index:</b> 58/100 (Δ ±0)<br/><b>Human cost:</b> No large-scale attack yet; Bawku ethnic conflict deaths<br/><b>Note:</b> NEW · Ghana's own ECOWAS Parliament submission: militants use N. Ghana for LOGISTICAL + MEDICAL support · galamsey (illegal gold mining) named #1 national security threat (KAIPTC) — organized crime/corruption nexus · Bawku Mamprusi-Kusasi conflict · Zongo-community radicalization risk · no confirmed large-scale attack inside Ghana yet<br/><b>Gov sources:</b> Ghana ECOWAS Parliament submission: Warned militants use N. Ghana for logistical/medical support; risk of escalation within borders | NCCRM (Act 1070, 2021): National Centre for Coordination of Early Warning; monitors crime, governance, terrorism; monthly reports to ECOWAS | NAIMOS anti-galamsey: 3 monitoring bases in Western Region (Ellembelle, Amenfi East, Ahanta West); galamsey ravaged 11 of 14 districts<br/><b>Mil leverage:</b> JNIM/ISGS: Rear-base logistics + medical staging in N. Ghana; galamsey recruitment pool [MED] | Ghanaian state: NCCRM early-warning (Act 1070); northern DSF redeployment; democratic legitimacy [MED] | Galamsey networks: Financiers + political-economic actors; environmental destruction; organized-crime ecosystem [MED]<br/><b>Econ leverage:</b> United States (Portfolio securities) [LOW]: $2.0B US securities (2024 TIC), debt-heavy — small against the galamsey shadow economy<br/><b>Assessment:</b> Ghana enters at 58 as a frontier state — not yet in open conflict but structurally exposed. The distinctive thread is the fusion you asked to track: galamsey is simultaneously the #1 crime/corruption problem and a potential security on-ramp, linking illegal mining, organized crime, and jihadist recruitment. Ghana's democratic institutions and early-warning architecture (NCCRM) are its resilience; its northern marginalization and galamsey grievances are the vulnerabilities.<br/><i>v15.0 · Week 12</i>]]></description><styleUrl>#s-military</styleUrl>
