<Placemark><name>🇨🇩 DRC — M23/Rwanda + ADF + Cobalt + Ebola</name>
<description><![CDATA[<b>DRC — M23/Rwanda + ADF + Cobalt + Ebola</b><br/><b>Subregion:</b> Central Africa<br/><b>Category:</b> MILITARY | <b>Domain:</b> Proxy War / Resource War<br/><b>Severity:</b> CRITICAL | <b>Status:</b> ESCALATING<br/><b>Index:</b> 82/100 (Δ ±0)<br/><b>Human cost:</b> 10,000+ since 2022; ADF killed 149 civ in Ituri last month (ACLED)<br/><b>Note:</b> UPDATED · ADF killed 149 civilians in Ituri last month (=Jan-Apr total combined, ACLED) · Ebola now in 4th province (Bundibugyo strain, WHO) · ADF shifting north from N.Kivu into Ituri = both violence hotspot + Ebola-response center · M23 took Uvira; FARDC killed M23 spokesman Ngoma in record drone campaign · DRC + M23 pledged comprehensive peace agreement by MID-AUGUST; both sides reinforcing South Kivu — possible imminent battle for Uvira<br/><b>Gov sources:</b> WHO: Confirmed Ebola (Bundibugyo virus) spread to 4th province; Ituri insecurity limiting containment | DRC Government / FARDC: Record drone/air campaign; killed M23 spokesman Willy Ngoma | G7 / Élysée: Critical Minerals Alliance targeting cobalt/rare-earth concentration<br/><b>Mil leverage:</b> Rwanda: M23 proxy — took Uvira; mineral-rich east control; drone supply [HIGH] | ADF (IS-affiliate): Ituri massacres; disrupting Ebola response; northward shift [HIGH] | DRC + US/UAE PMC: Cobalt (70% of reserves); FARDC CH-4/Anka drones [MED] | G7: Critical Minerals Alliance — de-risking supply [MED]<br/><b>Econ leverage:</b> China / G7 (Critical minerals) [HIGH]: ~70% of cobalt reserves; Kolwezi chemical chain; G7 Critical Minerals Alliance de-risking<br/><b>Assessment:</b> DRC rises to 82. The compounding factor is the ADF-Ebola convergence in Ituri: the same territory is the Islamist-violence hotspot and the epidemic epicenter, and the violence is actively preventing the epidemic response — a lethal feedback loop. Rwanda's M23 proxy (now holding Uvira) remains the 'hi' geopolitical lever; the ADF is the humanitarian accelerant.<br/><i>v15.0 · Week 12</i>]]></description><styleUrl>#s-military</styleUrl>
