<Placemark><name>🇭🇹 Haiti — Viv Ansanm / State Collapse</name>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Haiti — Viv Ansanm / State Collapse</b><br/><b>Subregion:</b> Caribbean<br/><b>Category:</b> MILITARY | <b>Domain:</b> Criminal Insurgency / State Collapse<br/><b>Severity:</b> CRITICAL | <b>Status:</b> ESCALATING<br/><b>Index:</b> 94/100 (Δ ±0)<br/><b>Human cost:</b> 16,000+ killed since 2022; 2,300 killed in 2026 alone<br/><b>Note:</b> NEW · Viv Ansanm controls ~70-90% of Port-au-Prince · US-designated FTO · no president since Moïse assassination (2021) · UN Gang Suppression Force deploying (&lt;1,000 of planned 5,550; Chad/Kenya) BUT badly underfunded · Defense Ministry cabinet director kidnapped · Gran Grif Artibonite massacres · Chérizier reframing as anti-elite 'revolutionaries'<br/><b>Gov sources:</b> UN Security Council: Res 2699/GSF authorization; Viv Ansanm sanctions listing (2653 Committee, 8 Jul 2025); Chérizier + Izo listed | US State Dept / DNI-NCTC: FTO + Specially Designated Global Terrorist (May 2025); $5M bounty on Chérizier; NCTC group profile | UNODC / IOM: UNODC: crisis increasingly regional (arms/drug trafficking); IOM: 1.5M IDPs, 'even more alarming phase'<br/><b>Mil leverage:</b> Viv Ansanm (Chérizier): ~90% capital control; strategic corridors to Artibonite/Centre; extortion/kidnapping economy; forced recruitment [HIGH] | UN Gang Suppression Force: Chad/Kenya troops — but &lt;1,000 deployed, badly underfunded [LOW] | Transitional govt (Fils-Aimé): No president since 2021; HNP + FAd'H outgunned [LOW] | US: FTO designation; $5M Chérizier bounty; funding decisions on the GSF [MED]<br/><b>Assessment:</b> Haiti enters at 94 — the Western Hemisphere's most acute security collapse. It is a criminal insurgency that has functionally displaced the state: no president, a transitional government winding down, security forces outgunned, and an underfunded, understrength international force as the only counterweight. The Pan-Africanist dimension is Viv Ansanm's ideological self-fashioning as defenders of the Black poor against 'oligarchs and colonial powers' — a narrative Crisis Group documents even as the gangs prey on the very communities they claim to represent.<br/><i>v15.0 · Week 12</i>]]></description><styleUrl>#s-military</styleUrl>
