<Placemark><name>🇯🇲 Jamaica — Security Turnaround (Counter-Case)</name>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Jamaica — Security Turnaround (Counter-Case)</b><br/><b>Subregion:</b> Caribbean<br/><b>Category:</b> MILITARY | <b>Domain:</b> Organized Crime / State Response<br/><b>Severity:</b> MEDIUM | <b>Status:</b> DE-ESCALATING<br/><b>Index:</b> 42/100 (Δ ±0)<br/><b>Human cost:</b> ~673 murders 2025 (31-yr low, -43%); 33 in Jan 2026 (record-low month)<br/><b>Note:</b> NEW · COUNTER-CASE (de-escalating) · 31-year murder low: ~673 in 2025 (-43%), 33 in Jan 2026 = lowest month since records began 2001 · built on 20+ States of Emergency since 2018 · ACLED warns SoEs don't durably suppress gangs + carry police-brutality costs · still among highest per-capita murder rates in hemisphere<br/><b>Gov sources:</b> Jamaica OPM / JCF: PM Holness: 33 murders Jan 2026 = lowest month since 2001; Plan Secure Jamaica framework | STATIN / JIS: ~673 murders 2025 = 31-year low, -43%; -32% shootings; official national statistics | US State Dept OSAC: JCF reported 666 murders Jan-Dec 27 2025 (-41.7%); still among highest per-capita in hemisphere<br/><b>Mil leverage:</b> Jamaican state (Holness): Plan Secure Jamaica; SoE powers; JDF-JCF joint ops; institutional reform [HIGH] | Gangs: Persistent but suppressed; extortion; deportee-linked networks [MED] | SoE mechanism: Temporary violence reduction — but ACLED: no durable gang suppression [MED]<br/><b>Assessment:</b> Jamaica enters at 42, trend down — the platform's clearest de-escalation and a methodological anchor: it proves the framework tracks improvement, not just crisis. The turnaround is real and government-data-verified, but fragile — built on emergency powers ACLED judges non-durable, and still leaving Jamaica among the hemisphere's highest per-capita murder rates. The counter-case to Haiti's collapse next door.<br/><i>v15.0 · Week 12</i>]]></description><styleUrl>#s-military</styleUrl>
