<Placemark><name>🇻🇪 Venezuela — US Intervention / Remote Coercion</name>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Venezuela — US Intervention / Remote Coercion</b><br/><b>Subregion:</b> South America<br/><b>Category:</b> MILITARY | <b>Domain:</b> Intervention / Occupation-by-Leverage<br/><b>Severity:</b> HIGH | <b>Status:</b> VOLATILE<br/><b>Index:</b> 71/100 (Δ +1)<br/><b>Human cost:</b> Op Absolute Resolve (Jan 3): Maduro security team largely killed; 32 Cuban soldiers killed; 7 US wounded<br/><b>Note:</b> NEW THEATER (backfilled) · Jan 3 2026: Operation Absolute Resolve — US strikes on Caracas, Maduro + Cilia Flores captured, flown to NY on USS IWO JIMA (2h28m op) · VP Delcy Rodríguez sworn interim · Trump: 'We\'re going to run the country' · naval armada + tanker blockade remain · $2B stranded-crude export deal; first $500M sale ($300M to Caracas) · May: Alex Saab deported · Jun: Tren de Aragua chief Niño Guerrero killed in JOINT US-Venezuela op · Jun: earthquakes; Mexico aid via Rodríguez call · USER WARGAME LAYER: 44-asset pre-war order of battle (Ford CSG, Iwo Jima ARG, El Libertador Iran-UAV hub, S-300 IADS, Amuay/El Palito) staged into master KML<br/><b>Gov sources:</b> US Congress (CRS): Administration notified Congress of 'non-international armed conflict' with cartels in Venezuela and beyond; War Powers resolutions (S.J.Res.83/90) considered, not passed | US Treasury TIC / DOJ: Maduro + Flores arraigned SDNY on narco-terrorism; $50M bounty claimed by US itself | China MFA / EU (Kallas): China demands Maduro's immediate release ('blatant use of force against a sovereign state'); EU-minus-Hungary calls for restraint under UN Charter | UK House of Commons Library: Cuba confirmed 32 soldiers killed; large part of Maduro's security team killed; legality questioned under international law<br/><b>Mil leverage:</b> United States: Finance/legal HIGH (user matrix confirmed): blockade + OFAC licensing + oil-sale mechanism + offshore armada — coercion without occupation [HIGH] | China: 80-84% of Venezuela's oil exports (direct/indirect) + $10B debt — the unresolved contradiction in the $100B investment plan [HIGH] | Rodríguez interim govt + generals: Colectivos/counterintel street presence; cooperation-for-survival (Saab handover, Guerrero op) [MED] | Russia + Iran: Diluent supply HIGH (naphtha/condensate); El Libertador UAV program; advisory footprint — degraded post-capture [MED]<br/><b>Econ leverage:</b> China (Export market) [HIGH]: 80-84% of oil exports direct/indirect; $10B debt; &gt;$1B/yr rebranded via Brazil (user matrix) | United States (Finance / legal / blockade) [HIGH]: OFAC licensing + tanker blockade + managed oil sales ($500M sold, $300M remitted); severe-discount scenario halves export value | Russia + Iran (Diluents / inputs) [HIGH]: Naphtha + condensate supply (Iran ~41.3 kbpd barter 2022-23); 15-yr PDVSA-Roszarubezhneft JV<br/><b>Assessment:</b> Venezuela enters at 71 with a backfilled arc — high but stable, because the kinetic phase ended in January and what remains is an occupation-by-leverage in uneasy equilibrium. The user's pre-war wargame layer proved predictive (it mapped the Iwo Jima ARG that carried Maduro out) and now anchors the theater's geography. The unresolved contradictions set the trajectory: China holds the export market the US plan needs; the generals hold the streets the transition needs; and the coercive model that secured control may be incompatible with the investment climate required to monetize it.<br/><i>v15.0 · Week 12</i>]]></description><styleUrl>#s-military</styleUrl>
