<Placemark><name>🇲🇽 Mexico — Cartel-FTO Confrontation / Sovereignty Squeeze</name>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Mexico — Cartel-FTO Confrontation / Sovereignty Squeeze</b><br/><b>Subregion:</b> North America<br/><b>Category:</b> POLITICAL | <b>Domain:</b> Coercive Diplomacy / Cartel War<br/><b>Severity:</b> HIGH | <b>Status:</b> ESCALATING<br/><b>Index:</b> 62/100 (Δ +1)<br/><b>Human cost:</b> Cartel violence ongoing; no US kinetic strikes on Mexican soil to date<br/><b>Note:</b> NEW THEATER (backfilled from W1) · APR 29 (=our W1): DOJ indicted 10 Mexican officials incl. SITTING Sinaloa Gov. Rubén Rocha Moya (AMLO ally, Morena), Sen. Inzunza, Culiacán mayor — extradition demanded · Nat'l Drug Control Strategy 2026: cartels = FTOs, fentanyl = WMD, extraterritorial-ops authority · Trump post-Maduro: 'We are going to start hitting land... The cartels are running Mexico' · Sheinbaum: charges 'political'; first public criticism of Amb. Johnson in 14 months; ~70% approval · cooperation continues: 10,000 troops to border, 90+ extraditions · Jun: Sheinbaum rejects Espriella labeling Mexican cartels military targets; warns vs Mexico as Nov-2026-midterm rhetoric<br/><b>Gov sources:</b> US DOJ / DEA (Cole): Apr 29: 10 officials charged incl. sitting Sinaloa governor — 'No one is above the law'; extradition requested | National Drug Control Strategy 2026: Cartels designated FTOs; fentanyl classified WMD; measurable compliance benchmarks; expanded extraterritorial authority | Sheinbaum govt: Rejected charges as political; 10,000 security forces deployed to border; 90+ extraditions delivered; record-low migration flows<br/><b>Mil leverage:</b> United States: FTO/WMD legal architecture + extraterritorial authority + tariff/USMCA-nonrenewal threat + indictment-extradition pressure [HIGH] | Sheinbaum government: Migration cooperation (Trump's signature win depends on it) + 80% of exports to US = mutual dependence + 70% approval [MED] | Cartels (Sinaloa/CJNG): Reduced fentanyl shipments under pressure — adaptive, not defeated; state-capture depth the indictments expose [MED] | Morena party dynamics: Rocha Moya = AMLO ally; extradition decision risks splintering the ruling party [MED]<br/><b>Assessment:</b> Mexico enters at 62, trend up. This is the hemisphere's most consequential slow-burn: the Venezuela precedent plus the FTO/WMD legal stack means the distance from indictments to kinetic action is shorter than it has ever been, while mutual dependence (migration for Trump, exports for Mexico) is the stabilizer neither side can afford to break. The Rocha Moya extradition decision is the fuse to watch — it forces Sheinbaum to choose between her party and her northern flank.<br/><i>v15.0 · Week 12</i>]]></description><styleUrl>#s-political</styleUrl>
