<Folder><name>Middle East</name><open>0</open>
<Placemark><name>🌐 US–Israel vs. Iran — Spike &amp; Settle</name>
<description><![CDATA[<b>US–Israel vs. Iran — Spike &amp; Settle</b><br/><b>Subregion:</b> Middle East<br/><b>Category:</b> MILITARY | <b>Domain:</b> Interstate War → Managed Standoff<br/><b>Severity:</b> CRITICAL | <b>Status:</b> VOLATILE<br/><b>Index:</b> 79/100 (Δ ±0)<br/><b>Human cost:</b> Khamenei killed in opening salvo; Gulf capitals struck<br/><b>Note:</b> Doha talks concluded (indirect only — Qatari+Pakistani mediators; Iran refused direct) · one-week "keep things quiet" understanding — clashes could erupt "right after July 4th" (Axios) · Qalibaf on state TV: "Sovereignty of the Strait of Hormuz lies with Iran and Oman" · $6B: goods-not-cash mechanism disputed; US denies any release · next round after Khamenei funeral ends JUL 9 · IRIB claims foreign ship ran aground off Iran-designated route<br/><b>Gov sources:</b> US CENTCOM: Confirmed 10-target strike; 'powerful response' | Bahrain/Kuwait govts: Condemned Iranian strikes as 'dangerous escalation' | Iran parliament (Azizi): Strait 'governed by Iran'; strike was 'ceasefire management' | Iran state TV (Qalibaf): 'Sovereignty of the Strait of Hormuz lies with Iran and Oman' — joint-administration + passage-fee claim after 60-day MOU | Qatar MOFA: 'Positive progress' on Islamabad MOU issues; next meeting after Khamenei funeral ends July 9; emergency communication channel agreed<br/><b>Mil leverage:</b> Iran (IRGC): Hormuz control + horizontal reach (Gulf capitals) + sole-demining claim [HIGH] | United States: Strike power + $300B gatekeeping + sanctions relief [HIGH] | Israel: Spoiler veto; Katz prepping independent strike [MED] | Qatar/GCC: $6B custodian; Doha venue; toll rejection [MED]<br/><b>Econ leverage:</b> Qatar / US (Frozen assets + reconstruction) [HIGH]: $6B goods-not-cash mechanism (disputed); $300B reconstruction gatekeeping<br/><b>Assessment:</b> Iran-US holds at 79 with the structure hardening beneath a fragile calm. Doha produced only a one-week quiet-period — with Axios flagging renewed clashes possible 'right after the 4th of July' — and Iran escalated doctrinally: chief negotiator Qalibaf declared on state television that 'sovereignty of the Strait of Hormuz lies with Iran and Oman,' formalizing the joint-administration and toll claim for when the 60-day MOU expires. The double cliff (July 4 truce expiry, July 9 funeral-end talks) makes this the tightest calendar on the board.<br/><i>v15.0 · Week 12</i>]]></description><styleUrl>#s-military</styleUrl>
