<Placemark><name>🇵🇸 Israel–Gaza War</name>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Israel–Gaza War</b><br/><b>Subregion:</b> Middle East<br/><b>Category:</b> MILITARY | <b>Domain:</b> Counterinsurgency<br/><b>Severity:</b> CRITICAL | <b>Status:</b> STALEMATE<br/><b>Index:</b> 77/100 (Δ ±0)<br/><b>Human cost:</b> 73,000+ Palestinians killed (UNRWA, mid-2026)<br/><b>Note:</b> Shaky ceasefire holds; J-Post: Israel 'running out of quality targets' · Board of Peace Mladenov demilitarization plan apparently rejected by Hamas · Gulf-capital competition w/ Iran $300B<br/><b>Gov sources:</b> UNRWA: 73,000+ Palestinian deaths (mid-2026) | Board of Peace (Mladenov): Gaza demilitarization plan apparently rejected by Hamas<br/><b>Mil leverage:</b> Israel: 'Unlimited' Gaza security-zone control; Yellow Line enforcement [HIGH] | Hamas: Refusal to disarm; rejected Mladenov plan; residual hostage/body leverage [MED] | Board of Peace / Gulf: $5B+ reconstruction capital (competing with Iran $300B) [MED]<br/><b>Assessment:</b> Gaza holds at 77. The frozen ceasefire persists; the J-Post's 'running out of targets' marker suggests the military phase is largely spent even as strikes continue. Both diplomatic strands are stuck: the Mladenov plan rejected, reconstruction gated behind an absent security framework.<br/><i>v15.0 · Week 12</i>]]></description><styleUrl>#s-military</styleUrl>
