<Placemark><name>🇱🇧 Lebanon — Framework Signed (Contested)</name>
<description><![CDATA[<b>Lebanon — Framework Signed (Contested)</b><br/><b>Subregion:</b> Middle East<br/><b>Category:</b> MILITARY | <b>Domain:</b> Framework → Disputed Implementation<br/><b>Severity:</b> HIGH | <b>Status:</b> VOLATILE<br/><b>Index:</b> 76/100 (Δ ±0)<br/><b>Human cost:</b> IDF Cpt. Hazutt killed; hundreds since Apr 17<br/><b>Note:</b> Trilateral framework SIGNED Jun 26 — IDF withdraws from 2 pilot zones, LAF oversees disarmament · Hezbollah (Qassem): 'null &amp; void' · Katz: not 'a millimeter' more · Haaretz: 'Gaza Strip 2' · permanent-deal odds 1.4% · Israeli drone strikes/artillery continued across the south (Nabatieh al-Fawqa, Bint Jbeil) despite framework; relief volunteers under fire · US told Iran at Doha it would "restrain Israel"; pilot-zone withdrawal framed as "first step"<br/><b>Gov sources:</b> US State Dept (Rubio): Announced framework as 'beginning of the beginning' | Israel (Katz): 'No territorial ambitions' but won't withdraw 'a millimeter' beyond pilot zones | Lebanese government: Signed; declared Hezbollah 'enemy of Lebanon'<br/><b>Mil leverage:</b> Israel: Occupation of S.Lebanon zone; pilot-zone withdrawal as chip [HIGH] | United States: Mediation; ties Lebanon to Iran track [HIGH] | Hezbollah: Spoiler veto — rejected framework as 'null &amp; void' [MED] | Lebanese Armed Forces: To receive pilot zones + oversee disarmament (untested) [MED]<br/><b>Assessment:</b> Lebanon holds at 76 — it rose because the framework got signed, but of its three negotiation strands one is signed, one collapsed (disarmament), and one stalled. The signed paper may institutionalize an indefinite Israeli presence rather than resolve anything.<br/><i>v15.0 · Week 12</i>]]></description><styleUrl>#s-military</styleUrl>
