<description><![CDATA[<b>Russia–Ukraine War</b><br/><b>Subregion:</b> Europe<br/><b>Category:</b> MILITARY | <b>Domain:</b> Interstate War<br/><b>Severity:</b> CRITICAL | <b>Status:</b> ESCALATING<br/><b>Index:</b> 84/100 (Δ ±0)<br/><b>Human cost:</b> ~1.4M Russian casualties (Ukraine est.); 250-300k Ukrainian<br/><b>Note:</b> ISW: Russia net −281 sq km Dec25-May26, offensive 'largely halted' not seasonal · Ukraine advancing at Pokrovsk · Putin resisting own economists' spending-cut warnings · Russia still grinding at Pokrovsk (Crisis Group: fall would disrupt Kyiv's entire eastern supply line) — watch item within the ISW net-loss frame<br/><b>Gov sources:</b> ISW / Critical Threats Project: Russia gained 40.64 sq km but lost 281.1 sq km Dec25-May26; 7.87% of 2025 pace | Ukraine General Staff: Record ~660-drone assault; Pokrovsk-direction advances<br/><b>Mil leverage:</b> Ukraine: Deep-strike drones halting ~40% of Russian oil exports + Flamingo missiles [HIGH] | Russia: Missile/drone barrage; but ground offensive largely halted [MED] | E3/EU/NATO: Weapons, financing, EU accession; NATO summit [MED] | US (Trump): Signaled Russian-oil re-sanctioning; swing broker [MED]<br/><b>Assessment:</b> Ukraine holds at 84. The headline is analytical: ISW's rigorous dataset shows Russia net-losing ground, converting 'first chance to win' from speculation to evidence-backed assessment. The Russian-economy wildcard — Putin overriding his own officials — determines the next quarter.<br/><i>v15.0 · Week 12</i>]]></description><styleUrl>#s-military</styleUrl>
